\fs45 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Workflows and Agents\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 In many real\uc0\u8208 world projects,\'a0choosing between a simple script, a deterministic workflow, a traditional chatbot, a retrieval\u8208 augmented generation (RAG) system, or a\'a0full\u8208 blown\'a0autonomous agent can be the difference between an elegant solution and an overengineered\
\
To make this choice clearer, consider four key factors: \
1-  The variability of your inputs\
2-  The complexity of the reasoning required\
3 - Any performance or compliance constraints\
4-  The ongoing maintenance burden.\
\
\'a0If your inputs are fully predictable and every possible output can be described in advance, a handful of lines of procedural code are often faster and cheaper\
\
Deterministic or\'a0semiautomated workflows. Here, the logic can be expressed as a finite set of steps or branches, and you know ahead of time where you might need human intervention or extra error handling\
\
Traditional chatbots\'a0or RAG systems occupy the next tier of complexity: they add natural language understanding and document retrieval but stop short of autonomous, multistep planning. If your primary need is to let users ask questions about a knowledge base\'97say, searching a product manual, a legal archive, or corporate wikis\'97a RAG system can embed documents into a vector store, retrieve relevant passages in response to a query, and generate coherent, context\uc0\u8208 aware answers. \
\
we reach\'a0autonomous agents\'97situations where neither simple code, nor rigid workflows, nor RAG suffice because inputs are unstructured, novel, or highly variable, and because you require dynamic, multistep planning or continuous learning from feedback\
\
Agents also excel when many subtasks must run in parallel\'97such as a security operations agent that simultaneously queries threat intelligence APIs, scans network telemetry, and performs sandbox analysis on suspicious binaries. Because agents operate asynchronously and reprioritize based on real\uc0\u8208 time data, they avoid the brittle \'93one\u8208 step\u8208 at\u8208 a\u8208 time\'94 nature of workflows or RAG systems.\
\
{{\NeXTGraphic Pasted Graphic 1.png \width28120 \height15840 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\

\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \

\fs28 \
Every path carries trade\uc0\u8208 offs. Pure code is cheap and fast but inflexible; workflows offer control but break down when inputs grow wildly variable; traditional chatbots or RAG are great for question\u8208 answering over documents but cannot orchestrate multistep actions; and agents are powerful but demanding \
\
Before choosing, ask: are my inputs unstructured or unpredictable? Do I need multistep planning that adapts to intermediate results? Can a document retrieval system suffice for my users\'92 information needs, or must the system decide and act autonomously  Will I want this system to improve itself over time with minimal human intervention? And can I tolerate the latency and maintenance burden of a foundation model?\
\
